    "updated_at": "2015-11-26T11:58:35Z",
    "body": "Hey I just want to point out that the `<webview>` does become transparent if we don't give a fixed (px) width and height on the tag's styles.\n\nIt seems that the issue has been fixed on the chromium source\n- [Issue 553378:   Chrome webview allowtransparency does not work correctly when webview or its parent containers are defined with exact widths and heights in px](https://code.google.com/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=553378&q=status%3Aunconfirmed&sort=-id&colspec=ID%20Stars%20Area%20Feature%20Status%20Summary%20Modified%20OS)\n- [Issue 529899: Webview transparency regression](https://code.google.com/p/chromium/issues/detail?id=529899)\n\nNot sure if the files mentioned on at the end of issue 529899 are part of atom or are compiled into the linked libs.\n\nOr what would be the process to patch Electron\n"
  }
